span.font: DPU/IPU (OS, UEFI) takes RedFish commands from a RedFish server on NIC BMC.

The user can interact with the NIC BMC directly (via its mgmt port, shown in blue) or by enabling a local RedFish "proxy" on the NIC BMC (shown in orange), whose role is to request commands from platform BMC's RedFish server (intended for the NIC) and submit them into its local RedFish server.
